  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>parsnip[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>in half lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into batons</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-9-copy-1699976945735-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-9-copy-1699976945735-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-9-copy-1699976945735-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-9-copy-1699976945735-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-9-copy-1699976945735-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> sausages </strong>to one side of a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Add the <strong>carrot</strong> and<strong> parsnip batons</strong> to the other side of the tray (cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>dried sage </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give the vegetables a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the sausages are cooked through</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-10-copy-1699976954715-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-10-copy-1699976954715-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-10-copy-1699976954715-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-10-copy-1699976954715-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-10-copy-1699976954715-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your<strong> potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender then drain and leave to steam dry (reserve the pot!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1701172850076-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1701172850076-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1701172850076-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1701172850076-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1701172850076-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and<strong> </strong>50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> [100ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Cook for 7-8 min or until soft and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-9-1699976969464-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-9-1699976969464-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-9-1699976969464-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-9-1699976969464-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-9-1699976969464-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Once the onion is soft, add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pan</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until the onion is coated in the flour</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-9-1699976988319-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-9-1699976988319-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-9-1699976988319-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-9-1699976988319-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-9-1699976988319-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion is coated in the flour, add your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>to the pan with your <strong>cranberry sauce </strong>and 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min further or until slightly thickened – this is your<strong> cranberry gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-9-1699976998435-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-9-1699976998435-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
