          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-9-1699976998435-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>to the reserved pot with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>milk</strong>,<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining dried sage</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook over a low heat until the butter has melted and the milk is warmed through</p><p>Once the milk is warmed through, add the <strong>drained potato</strong> and mash until smooth – this is your <strong>sage mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
